@alreadydone I am happy if you want to merge your extension into this one: I only looked briefly at the new results, but they seem great!

I think that maybe we should also re-think a splitting of the PR for merging.  The initial input was providing a `NoZeroDivisors` instance for Lindemann-Weierstrass.  Ideally, we would be able to split out a shortcut to this result that can be merged relatively early on, while keeping all the goodies in the "main" PR.

Does this seem reasonable?

